==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|el}} {{term|ουτοπία|tr=[[ootopia]]||no (such) place|sc=Grek}}, a term coined by [[w:Thomas More|Sir Thomas More]], from {{etyl|grc}} prefix {{term|ου|tr=[[oo]]||not, no|sc=Grek|lang=grc}} + {{term|τόπος|tr=[[topos]]||place, region, metaph. occasion, opportunity|sc=Grek|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/juˈtopiə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[world]] in which everything and everyone works in perfect harmony.
# The [[satirical]] [[treatise]] on government by [[w:Thomas More|Sir Thomas More]], from which the term was coined.

